---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Project: Panic Catchup | Welcome">
  <div class="flex flex-col items-center justify-center min-h-[75vh] px-4 sm:px-6">
    <div class="max-w-3xl w-full bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-2xl shadow-xl p-8 sm:p-12 transition-colors duration-300">
      
      <!-- Title Section -->
      <div class="text-center mb-10 border-b border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 pb-8">
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold mb-4 tracking-tight text-gray-900 dark:text-white transition-colors duration-300">
          Project: Panic Catchup
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xl font-medium text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 transition-colors duration-300">
          High-Density Narrative Summaries for returning readers.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Disclaimer Section -->
      <div class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none mb-12 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 transition-colors duration-300">
        <p><strong>Welcome to Project: Panic Catchup.</strong><br/>
        This project was born from my own needs as an avid sci-fi and fantasy reader of very long series. Sometimes we have to wait years for a new installment. Other times we have read 2,000 pages of a story and just need a break. And other times, life simply gets in the way. In any case, it is easy to forget the characters, details, and intricate plot lines of these beloved stories. I created this archive to help us all out.</p>

        <p><strong>The Goal is to Encourage Reading, Not Skip It.</strong><br/>
        This project is intended to support authors and is in no way meant to undermine their works. These novels are popular for a reason—writers pour their souls into these stories. Therefore, these summaries are intentionally brief and "soulless" because they are NOT meant to replace the actual reading experience. They are purely concrete refreshers designed to reactivate the journeys that we readers have already gone on. The authors are the ones who write the magic into these works. Go support them by buying their books, and even better, support them by shopping at your local bookstores and libraries.</p>

        <p><strong>Fair Use & Copyright Disclaimer</strong><br/>
        <em>The summaries provided on this site are transformative, educational reference materials created under the Fair Use doctrine (17 U.S.C. § 107). They consist solely of factual, high-level plot synopses and do not reproduce the authors' original prose, dialogue, or artistic expression. This project does not serve as a market substitute for the original novels; its target audience consists exclusively of returning readers who have already purchased and consumed the original works. All character names, world-building elements, and cover art concepts belong entirely to their respective authors and publishers.</em></p>

        <p><strong>A Note on AI Generation</strong><br/>
        <em>I personally own, and have read, every single book featured in this archive. To make a project of this scale possible, I used AI purely as a summarization tool to distill thousands of pages down into concrete bullet points. However, every summary was audited and curated by a human (me) to ensure accuracy and respect for the source material.</em></p>
      </div>

      <!-- Enter Button -->
      <div class="flex justify-center">
        <a 
          href="/archive" 
          class="inline-flex items-center px-10 py-5 bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-500 text-white text-lg font-bold uppercase tracking-widest rounded-xl shadow-lg transition-all hover:scale-105 active:scale-95 focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-400 focus:ring-offset-2 focus:ring-offset-gray-50 dark:focus:ring-offset-gray-900"
        >
          Enter the Archive
          <svg class="w-6 h-6 ml-3" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M14 5l7 7m0 0l-7 7m7-7H3" />
          </svg>
        </a>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
